You'll be needing a lot of these.

Equip the Resonating Wand during the night, and look for glowing lights coming off the ground. Dig down to near bedrock, and use the wand to find the Rock Crystals in the wall.

*Warning* You will need a diamond or better pick to mine these without destroying the fragile crystals!
A big deep magic hole

Lets get started on... STAR POWER!

To craft the resonating wand, you'll need to find an Astral Sorcery shrine. There are many types of shrines, but two types contain the big floating Collector Crystals you will need. Some show up underground, so congrats if you find one. The others are large marble structures that appear above ground. If you dig into the floor, you'll find the big crystal, as well as some chests.

To make the wand, place a crafting table down, which will cause a beam of light to extend from the crystal towards the table. Then put the ingredients in, and you can craft the wand.
It's time to start making mana
Will flower power threaten my masculinity?
Now you can actually start doing useful things

Start doing stuff with star power.

To craft this table, you'll need to do the same you did with the resonating wand - find a shrine with a floating Collector Crystal, place down a workbench and wait for the beam of light, then put the ingredients into the crafting table. Congrats, you now have a luminous crafting table!
It's steel, but more... earthy
Time to make some fancy stuff

Did this REALLY come from a star?

To make starmetal ore, place iron ore near a collector crystal. Then with the linking tool in hand, right click the crystal then right click the iron ore. After a short period, the iron ore will turn into starmetal ore. You can then mine it, and place down new iron ore without re-linking.
Bigger better more starry crystals

Right click the Luminous Crafting Table with your resonating wand to channel starlight and complete the craft.

Throw Aquamarines into the Lightwell to generate Starlight. This will eventually break the aquamarine.

You can also use Rock Crystals, but they will also break down, so be careful not to waste them.

Pump me full of starlight, baby.

Another multiblock temple structure that will infuse items with liquid starlight. Once you unlock the Containment Chalice, this thing really becomes powerful.
Feel the power
You'll need an arc furnace to make this. Start making steel.
You're gonna need some alloys. There is other methods to create these alloys, but some of them won't be available early on.
A place to cook! All the equipment your heart could desire

Now you can control starlight.

Right click a starlight source (such as a Crystal in a temple) and then link it to targets by right clicking the target.

Unequip the Linking Tool to stop linking.

Power!

Give it solid fuel and water, then hook it up to some thing that needs (or stores) power.
Your stuff is now binary.
Making things... with computers
This thing is gonna need power. Here's how you hook it up
You need an automatic way to convert items into digital form. Connect a machine or pipe to this block, and things that go into it will automatically go into the ME system. Wow!

A standalone network without a controller (known as an ad-hoc network) can only support 8 channels - more simply, only 8 devices can be connected.

With an ME Controller, you can vastly increase the amount of connected devices. Each face of the controller provides 32 channels, which you'll need either Dense ME cables or a p2p device (more on that later) to get out directly. 

Multiple ME controllers can also be connected as a multiblock, when you start needing more than 96+ channels.

The ME controller also serves a dual purpose of being an energy input device, so you'll no longer need the energy acceptor.

This device is interesting. It allows you to make recipes, either normal crafting or "processing", which can then be put into an interface. When this interface is connected to a molecular assembler you can automatically craft items with normal crafting recipes.

But more interestingly, when you connect the interface to some kind of machine or other complex setup, you can input arbitrary ingredients and get arbitrary outputs, fo creating items without normal crafting recipes. I'll leave you to figure out the rest.

When connected to an interface that has encoded patterns in it, this will automatically craft the items on-demand. It can be sped up with acceleration cards. It can also have multiple interfaces connected to it, if you want more than 8 recipes. Note, however, that it can always only craft one item at a time.

You're gonna need gears. Until you figure out a better methods, you'll have to cast them directly.

To make the cast, use a stone gear and pour gold or aluminum brass over it from the smeltery.

The luminous crafting table only lets you craft the most basic of Astral sorcery items. Time to upgrade.

The Starlight Crafting Table is the first multi-block structure of AS, and opens up a lot more, and more interesting, crafting options.

See the Astral Sorcery book for multiblock shape, and remember it needs to be night for enough starlight to craft the table!

Point this at the sky and right click during the night to find Temples and Shrines in the area.

Hold shift and drag the correct icon onto a star to be able to see it while moving.
Craft with lots of things

The Improved Blast Furnace can be automated, and have 'Blast Furnace Preheaters' added beside it to increase it's speed (they need to be powered!)
Time for another table upgrade. You'll need more marble to expand the multi-block temple you are building, but it's up to you this time to gather all that.

One of the big problems with multiplayer minecraft is players like to build far apart sometimes. This handy dandy device allows you to traverse the stars to visit any other celestial gateway at the speed of starlight!
